  "texts": [
    "The use of large-scale datasets in natural language processing (NLP) introduces privacy risks, especially in sensitive domains like healthcare and finance.",
    "To protect user data and enable robust model training, it is essential to develop privacy-preserving techniques such as federated learning, differential privacy, and homomorphic encryption.",
    "A comprehensive roadmap should focus on creating frameworks that comply with regulations like the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and exploring privacy-enhancing technologies (PETs), such as privacy-as-aservice platforms, for handling sensitive data.",
    "Integrating regular privacy audits ensures compliance, transparency, and sustained user trust in these systems.",
    "Additionally, scalability and sustainable deployment solutions are crucial for ensuring the long-term success of these technologies."
  ],
